# Walkthrough: Full-Screen Hero Animation Landing Page

I have expanded the hero frames animation to cover the entire background of the Hero Section and simplified the [Index](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/pages/Index.tsx#14-48) page to make it a focused landing page.

## Changes Made

### Component Refactoring
Modified [HeroSection.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/components/HeroSection.tsx) to:
- Move the [FrameAnimation](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/components/HeroSection.tsx#10-98) from the title to the section background.
- Apply `absolute inset-0` and `object-cover` to the animation canvas.
- Add a backdrop blur and background tint for improved text readability.
- Scale and adjust brightness for a premium aesthetic.

### Landing Page Simplification
Updated [Index.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/pages/Index.tsx) to:
- Comment out secondary sections (`IdentitySection`, `ExecutionStack`, etc.).
- The page now focuses purely on the Hero Section experience.

